- Use `forwardRef` to resolve circular dependencies in NestJS.
- Example of using `forwardRef`: 
  ```typescript
  import { Module, forwardRef } from '@nestjs/common';
  import { AService } from './a.service';
  import { BService } from './b.service';

  @Module({
    providers: [AService],
    exports: [AService]
  })
  export class AModule {}

  @Module({
    imports: [forwardRef(() => AModule)],
    providers: [BService],
    exports: [BService]
  })
  export class BModule {}
  ```
- Ensure you are using the latest version of NestJS for optimal functionality and security.
- Key config options include `imports`, `providers`, and `exports` in module definitions.
